parameters: \n<???>Yeah♥ I've been waiting for you, old man♥

\n<\N[3]>Now, as promised, tell me the cause and how to
stop the \c[2]phenomenon of madness\c[0].
\n<???>Huh? Did I promise you something like that?
\n<\N[3]>N-No... Well, since I've come this far...

\n<???>I promised that we would play together next time
we meet♥ That's why you came, right?

\n<\N[3]>Ugh...! Then what do I have to do to get an
answer!?

\n<???>Hehehe♥ If you have something you want to ask,
just make sure to \c[2]make me understand\c[0],
just like before♥

\n<\N[3]>...Then it's a promise. How to stop the phenomenon
of madness, and just who exactly are you all?
\n<\N[3]>If you lose, I'll make you give me the answer.

\n<???>I'm asking for two things, so it would be tough if
I lose, you know? ♥ Are you really okay with that?
♥

\n<\N[3]>...If I've come this far, there's no way I can
back down. If I lose, I'll do as you wish.

\n<???>You really intend to win, huh? Alright, it's a
promise. Let's have a real match, old man.

\n<\N[3]>...This is the last one...! I need to focus, I
absolutely have to stop it...!

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>You're doing great, old man♥ Your faithful
dedication to desire is so cool♥

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Hmm? Is it working? ♥ The love of an old man has
surely been conveyed, right? ♥

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>...Hehehe, it seems to have an effect, but it's
still a little unsatisfying, isn't it? ♥ This is
your last chance, if you can still maintain your
sanity in this state... ♥

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Reason or instinct. I'll show you the old man's
seriousness ♥
ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Ahh...♥ Hehehe, it felt good, didn't it, old man♥

\n<\N[3]>...I'm sorry, when reason flies out the window, I
can't control myself... Is your body okay?
ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>You don't need to worry, it's okay ♥ Thank you.

\n<\N[3]>...Are you...are you causing the phenomenon of
madness?

ルナ\SE[surprise]\n<???>Hm? Ah, it's a promise, right? Well, I guess it's
half right and half wrong?

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Do you know the law of universal gravitation? An
object with a larger mass has a corresponding
gravitational force according to its size.

\n<\N[3]>...If it's just something I learned in school as a
student...does it have any relevance?

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Well then, do you know about the weight of the
soul? It's the theory proposed by Dr. Duncan
MacDougall that the weight of a human soul is 21
grams.
\n<\N[3]>...Weight of the soul...? Does such a thing exist?

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Hehehe♥ Well? It seems that they measured the
weight ratio between before and immediately after
death, but there's also a theory that says it
became lighter due to evaporation because body
temperature temporarily rises when life activity
stops.

\n<\N[3]>...So...what exactly is the connection between all
of this?

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Hmm, you're so impatient. For example, if we
assume that there is a substance called a soul,
then as a material, it must have mass.

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Let's say, hypothetically, that there is a world
where souls gather. In other words, a space
similar to the afterlife exists. What do you think
would happen if a large mass were to occur there?

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>...Uncle, you were definitely sleeping during
class, right...?

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>Gravitational force is proportional to the mass of
an object. In other words, a soul with a larger
\c[2]mass\c[0] has the power to pull
\c[2]souls\c[0] with smaller \c[2]masses\c[0].

\n<\N[3]>...So...in other words...the story is that your
soul has a large mass...?

ルナ\SE[default]\n<???>As a result, it happened that way, and that is
exactly what became the cause of this phenomenon.
\c[2]After Luna's death,\c[0] there was someone
who gave her soul mass.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>...Uncle, did you think this strange phenomenon
was caused by some kind of virus or bacteria...?
Well, it's understandable if you find it hard to
believe.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>...Luna is here because someone, unbelievably,
took that ridiculous idea seriously and actually
succeeded in executing that plan to bring the dead
back to this world.

\n<\N[3]>...Could it be...then the documents that fell
earlier...and this underground facility...

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Without madness, success would be impossible. That
person remained obsessed with that plan until the
end and succeeded...

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>But, it's meaningless if you don't know about the
success. His failure was not realizing that Luna
had already manifested.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>By gathering the fragments of Luna's lost
memories, it was already too late when they
realized it. Now, that person is like a massive
gravity for Luna.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>If you try to stop or get close, you'll be
absorbed and broken. If that happens, it will be
even harder to gather the fragments... I can't
stop Luna or get close to her.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>...But, Luna... Anyway, the direct cause of the
phenomenon is this device ahead. It's called the
Manifestation Device.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>A device created as part of a plan to eventually
bring the dead back to life and manifest them in
this world... It was made and used as a stepping
stone for the resurrection of the deceased.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Of course, it was a plan that came with danger.
Unless there is a means to completely control such
immense power, one should not touch it. It's
because we ended up averting our eyes from such
obvious things...

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>It's about the \c[2]universal unconscious
realm\c[0], which is considered to be the dwelling
place of souls. In simple terms, it's the
\c[2]unconscious realm\c[0] that we are not aware
of in our everyday perception and cannot perceive.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Physically interfering here is also interfering
with the danger that we did not recognize. It's a
powerful force that immediately engulfs you if you
come into contact with it, like unconscious
desires, wishes, and strong thoughts.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>By now, you should understand, right? The
\c[2]Madness Transformation Phenomenon\c[0] is the
manifestation of this \c[2]Sea of
Unconsciousness\c[0] through physical
interference.

\n<\N[3]>...A device that materializes the unconscious...
And a phenomenon where one is absorbed by the
power generated by it, and their sanity is
destroyed... That is the phenomenon of madness.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Yes, Luna and the others are just a
\c[2]trigger\c[0]. They are the materialized
unconscious that erodes the rationality of those
who come into contact with it, leading them into
the sea of the unconscious.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>However, Luna and the others are merely the
catalysts for the phenomenon manifested by the
Manifestation Device.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>In other words, the way to stop the phenomenon is
to \c[2]stop the device\c[0]. Now, let's answer
another question. What is Luna and the others'
true identity...

\n<\N[3]>No way... Are you... the soul of the deceased...
just like you...?

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Well, that's not necessarily the case. Indeed,
Luna is the \c[2]core\c[0] of a soul that sank
into the sea of unconsciousness after death.
Because they have been materialized, they possess
clear personalities, wills, and physical forms.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>But in the real world, memories and emotions that
have been separated by the ego can sometimes form
as a single \c[2]thought form\c[0]. The
Manifestation Device is what materializes these
souls and thought forms, and they refer to them as
\c[2]thought bodies\c[0]. They called me [N_1].

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Whether the origin of the manifested thought
bodies is \c[2]souls\c[0] or a singular
\c[2]thought\c[0], Luna doesn't know either. It's
difficult to accept because it wouldn't have
appeared so clearly without strong thoughts.
There's no doubt that it happened.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>This world is formed by the desires born from
distorted thoughts. However, the \c[2]people\c[0]
who serve as the origin of these thoughts
definitely existed somewhere. Whether it was in
the past or the future is uncertain, but their
existence is certain.

\n<\N[3]>I see... So the cause of the phenomenon of madness
is the Manifestation Device, and you all are the
manifested thought forms created by that device.

\n<\N[3]>In any case, the root cause is the Manifestation
Device. If we stop it, the phenomenon will
cease... You all...

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Luna and the others will disappear. To be precise,
they will return to the realm of universal
unconsciousness. However, the fact that they are
manifesting in this way itself is unnatural, so
this is the correct form.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>There is no fear or regret in disappearing.
Because we are just thought forms, we don't have
the emotions that normal people have towards life.
We are nothing more than illusions created by
fragments.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>But... there is one thing... I want to ask of you,
sir... Will you listen?

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>...There is definitely someone ahead... I want you
to stop that person. Like I said earlier, Luna
cannot do it.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>This space is the void within Luna's
consciousness. From now on, we will return to the
real world, to the true underground facility,
where we should be able to meet that person.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Be careful. That person is neither a thought form
like Luna and the others, nor just a person who
has gone mad.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>The first madman, a powerful thought that spans
two worlds... no, a mass of grudges.

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>Only you who have come this far can stop it... an
unstoppable existence... so please...

ルナ\SE[cry]\n<???>...It seems like I used too much power... um, one
last request... please take care of it.
And so, another madman was born from that town.

The city of Sakuhai continued to decline as a city
of madmen, and eventually the government
prohibited entry into it.

At the center of the place where the phenomenon of
madness occurred, there is still a deep darkness
spreading...
